01:31:41,100 --> 01:31:44,320
 I have to say I'm glad Croatia is standing out

3337
01:31:44,320 --> 01:31:45,580
 in

3338
01:31:45,580 --> 01:31:46,660
 in crowd

3339
01:31:46,660 --> 01:31:49,020
 being here

3340
01:31:49,020 --> 01:31:50,280
 talking about

3341
01:31:50,280 --> 01:31:50,640
 the

3342
01:31:50,640 --> 01:31:52,720
 Euro adoption

3343
01:31:52,720 --> 01:31:54,400
 brings back

3344
01:31:54,400 --> 01:31:56,560
 not so distant memories

3345
01:31:56,560 --> 01:31:58,440
 from when Slovakia perhaps

3346
01:31:58,440 --> 01:32:00,760
 surprisingly for some

3347
01:32:00,760 --> 01:32:02,820
 said it signs it on

3348
01:32:02,820 --> 01:32:04,440
 join the Euro area

3349
01:32:04,440 --> 01:32:06,320
 a very ambitious goal

3350
01:32:06,320 --> 01:32:08,520
 that we reach in

3351
01:32:08,520 --> 01:32:09,060
 January

3352
01:32:09,060 --> 01:32:10,280
 2009

3353
01:32:10,280 --> 01:32:13,500
 so how did we get in

3354
01:32:13,500 --> 01:32:15,340
 and what did it take

3355
01:32:15,340 --> 01:32:19,100
 the road is really bumpy

3356
01:32:19,100 --> 01:32:20,000
 slippery

3357
01:32:20,000 --> 01:32:21,280
 and tricky

3358
01:32:21,280 --> 01:32:26,600
 I could entertain you for hours about our inflation costs

3359
01:32:26,600 --> 01:32:28,500
 I mean inflation sustainability

3360
01:32:28,500 --> 01:32:30,300
 before we got in

3361
01:32:30,300 --> 01:32:37,780
 there's a need to have a broad intersocietal debate about the costs and benefits of Euro adoption

3362
01:32:37,780 --> 01:32:52,080
 such debate should result in a firm commitment and support for the Euro from both the general public and the political elites may come in handy as well

3363
01:32:52,080 --> 01:32:53,300
 as well

3364
01:32:53,300 --> 01:32:57,980
 this however doesn't come easy or for free

3365
01:32:57,980 --> 01:33:05,300
 one government term is not enough to achieve this complex task

3366
01:33:05,300 --> 01:33:08,860
 this is a task for the long haul

3367
01:33:08,860 --> 01:33:12,300
 political consensus is therefore essential

3368
01:33:12,300 --> 01:33:15,640
 the pro-integration appetite

3369
01:33:15,640 --> 01:33:25,360
 in my country Slovakia grew out of an era during which Slovakia was on brink of a severe economic and financial crisis

3370
01:33:25,360 --> 01:33:27,740
 as well as international isolation

3371
01:33:27,740 --> 01:33:42,900
 I'm speaking of late 1990s when my country was infamously labeled ugly dougly by the former US secretary for example and it was a wake-up call for us

3372
01:33:42,900 --> 01:33:51,360
 in the former New Year's thanks to the will of the people and commitment of successive governments

3373
01:33:51,360 --> 01:34:00,260
 Slovakia shook off the nasty nickname and became a trusted member of the European Union and the Euro area

3374
01:34:00,260 --> 01:34:04,500
 it was all the work and energy

3375
01:34:04,500 --> 01:34:11,200
 the support for the Euro post-adoption grew even stronger

3376
01:34:11,200 --> 01:34:13,200
 which is a rather uncommon

3377
01:34:13,200 --> 01:34:15,200
 but all more welcome

3378
01:34:15,200 --> 01:34:17,200
 development

3379
01:34:17,200 --> 01:34:19,200
 fulfilling the accession criteria

3380
01:34:19,200 --> 01:34:24,200
 is however not always really not always straightforward

3381
01:34:24,200 --> 01:34:34,200
 from my experience the ERM-2 is a system which is not tailored for the small open catching up economies like ours

3382
01:34:34,200 --> 01:34:40,200
 Slovakia had to revalue its exchange rate parity twice before this year

3383
01:34:40,200 --> 01:34:48,200
 It is not appropriate for economies like ours to linger in the ERM-2 for the too long time

3384
01:34:48,200 --> 01:34:54,200
 What were the main benefits and costs of adapting the Euro?

3385
01:34:54,200 --> 01:35:00,200
 In our case, and it's important to highlight that we joined the Euro at a really very difficult time, a time of crisis

3386
01:35:00,200 --> 01:35:14,200
 With this in mind, Euro adoption had imminent effects both positive and negative

3387
01:35:14,200 --> 01:35:18,200
 Please, we have to travel in time in 2009

3388
01:35:18,200 --> 01:35:22,200
 Switching of currencies led to savings of transactions costs

3389
01:35:22,200 --> 01:35:32,200
 For example, however, it also meant losing the important tool of independent monetary policy

3390
01:35:32,200 --> 01:35:40,200
 Several studies now confirm that had Slovakia kept the floating currency regime during the recession in 2009

3391
01:35:40,200 --> 01:35:48,200
 The economy would have been temporarily better off by roughly 2% of GDP

3392
01:35:48,200 --> 01:35:56,200
 Overall, however, the effects of joining the Eurozone proved to be significantly positive

3393
01:35:56,200 --> 01:36:04,200
 According to our calculations, joined the Euro increased our GDP by more than 10%

3394
01:36:04,200 --> 01:36:12,200
 About two-thirds of this positive effect came even before the actual adoption of the single currency

3395
01:36:12,200 --> 01:36:14,200
 I mean the so-called anticipation effect

3396
01:36:14,200 --> 01:36:26,200
 The total impact of joining the European Union and the Euro was more than 20% of GDP in our case

3397
01:36:26,200 --> 01:36:34,200
 The Euro area membership boosted our exports and accelerated our convergence

3398
01:36:34,200 --> 01:36:42,200
 Perhaps even more importantly, however, by joining the Eurozone, Slovakia got a seat at the table

3399
01:36:42,200 --> 01:36:49,200
 Maybe not at the head of the table, but let's not get into that right now

3400
01:36:49,200 --> 01:37:01,200
 Sitting around that table, like it, no, not, means your voice and importance in Europe gets stronger

3401
01:37:01,200 --> 01:37:10,200
 Rises Slovakia, still a relatively new kid on the block, with a small, open economy, is in many ways

3402
01:37:10,200 --> 01:37:14,200
 A voice that bridges the gap between ins and outs

3403
01:37:14,200 --> 01:37:20,200
 We do understand that the Eurozone has to offer benefits to all its members

3404
01:37:20,200 --> 01:37:23,200
 Even the prospective ones

3405
01:37:23,200 --> 01:37:29,200
 During the crisis, the Euro provided the necessary price stability and collective strength

3406
01:37:29,200 --> 01:37:34,200
 The establishment of the banking union is one of the best examples

3407
01:37:34,200 --> 01:37:41,200
 With the crisis behind us and a window of opportunities slowly closing

3408
01:37:41,200 --> 01:37:49,200
 It's a time to look to the future and complete the missing elements of the Eurozone architecture

3409
01:37:49,200 --> 01:37:56,200
 We must make it more resilient and prosperous for decades to come, for all

3410
01:37:56,200 --> 01:38:03,200
 Make it accessible and attractive for states that we are willing to participate

3411
01:38:03,200 --> 01:38:09,200
 There are several things we need to do in that respect

3412
01:38:09,200 --> 01:38:18,200
 We have to complete the banking union in order to break the bank's sovereign nexus once and for all

3413
01:38:18,200 --> 01:38:30,200
 We have to get the capital markets union up and running to enhance private risk sharing and provide businesses with greater choice of funding

3414
01:38:30,200 --> 01:38:40,200
 And we have to build a fiscal capacity to compensate the loss of national monetary policy with a shield against asymmetric shocks

3415
01:38:40,200 --> 01:38:51,200
 We have to improve our fiscal rule book to make our fiscal rules simpler and more predictable

3416
01:38:51,200 --> 01:38:57,200
 And we have to design a smart and fair enforcement mechanism for these rules

3417
01:38:57,200 --> 01:38:59,200
 And finally, what we have to do?

3418
01:38:59,200 --> 01:39:07,200
 We have to restore the credibility of the no bailout rule and design a sovereign debt restructuring framework

3419
01:39:07,200 --> 01:39:12,200
 Even if some big players feel no love for that

3420
01:39:12,200 --> 01:39:19,200
 This is a package that I do believe contains all the missing pieces of the puzzle

3421
01:39:19,200 --> 01:39:24,200
 It balances the still necessary risk reduction with risk sharing

3422
01:39:24,200 --> 01:39:32,200
 To achieve a full-fledged banking union, reducing risks by resolving legacy issues from the crisis

3423
01:39:32,200 --> 01:39:44,200
 The high level of NPLs and sovereign exposures in domestic banks must go hand in hand with work on setting-ups of EDIS

3424
01:39:44,200 --> 01:39:51,200
 Here, I support the Commission's new proposal on EDIS, which provides a pragmatic way forward

3425
01:39:51,200 --> 01:40:04,200
 On the fiscal front, our rule book needs to be improved, simplified and most importantly credibly enforced

3426
01:40:04,200 --> 01:40:12,200
 If a supervising body is not up for the task, let's give markets the power to decide

3427
01:40:12,200 --> 01:40:19,200
 Here, sovereign debt restructuring framework could help markets to reinforce fiscal discipline

3428
01:40:19,200 --> 01:40:27,200
 As well as provide an orderly way to restructure public debt if it becomes unmanageable

3429
01:40:27,200 --> 01:40:31,200
 However, markets can also be ruthless

3430
01:40:31,200 --> 01:40:37,200
 Thankfully, we can put checks on the market and manage its overreaction

3431
01:40:37,200 --> 01:40:46,200
 Not having control over one's monetary policy can be costly, particularly during a cyclical downturn

3432
01:40:46,200 --> 01:40:56,200
 A centralised fiscal capacity designed to cushion asymmetric shocks would effectively compensate this loss

3433
01:40:56,200 --> 01:41:00,200
 Limiting the potential market backlash

3434
01:41:00,200 --> 01:41:03,200
 Several instruments have been proposed

3435
01:41:03,200 --> 01:41:11,200
 As I like to say, it doesn't matter what is the colour of the umbrella as long as it stops the rain

3436
01:41:11,200 --> 01:41:19,200
 There is a lot of work, really, a lot of work to be done

3437
01:41:19,200 --> 01:41:30,200
 Ladies and gentlemen, the next few years will be crucial for Croatia, for Slovakia, for Europe as a whole

3438
01:41:30,200 --> 01:41:33,200
 We all have homework to do

3439
01:41:33,200 --> 01:41:44,200
 I would like to encourage you to keep up your ambition and continue taking necessary, sometimes difficult steps to achieve your goal

3440
01:41:44,200 --> 01:41:55,200
 My promise is that I will do everything in my powers to make the Eurozone your future destination, I hope

3441
01:41:55,200 --> 01:42:01,200
 A more accommodating, balanced and stable house-place body

3442
01:42:01,200 --> 01:42:08,200
 For now, our voice is also your voice and you can count on that

3443
01:42:08,200 --> 01:42:09,200
 Hvala

3444
01:42:09,200 --> 01:42:11,200
 Hvala

3445
01:42:11,200 --> 01:42:13,200
 Hvala

3446
01:42:13,200 --> 01:42:15,200
 Hvala

3447
01:42:15,200 --> 01:42:16,200
 Hvala

3448
01:42:16,200 --> 01:42:17,200
 Hvala.

3449
01:42:46,200 --> 01:42:48,200
 Hvala.

3450
01:43:16,200 --> 01:43:25,980
 S Ljubljanske univerze i naše kolegu sa Hrvatske televizije Željka Karduma koji će i moderirati ovaj panel.

3451
01:43:46,200 --> 01:44:01,580
 Početane dame i gospodo, evo čuli smo jedan prekrasno zapravo uvodni govor od gospodina Petra Kažimira, a zaista je bio to po srdečanu ukazao na sve ono kroz što je Slovačka zapravo prošla i bila spremna za proći.

3452
01:44:01,580 --> 01:44:11,620
 Ono što bih htio posebno istaknuti uvijekom ovog panela je da ovdje imamo iskustva od dviju zemalja koje su prolazile i uvodile euro u različitim ciklusima.

3453
01:44:11,780 --> 01:44:19,580
 Dakle, Slovenija kad je ciklus još bio uzlazan i Slovačka kad je lagano padao.

3454
01:44:19,580 --> 01:44:39,080
 Dakle, imamo iskustva od ljudi, praktičara koji su bili ovdje, koji su bili u trenutku uvođenja Jugra, čuli smo dakle već izlaganje ministra financija Slovačke, koji je i prije, možda nije spomenuo čak i prije nego što je bio imeno na mjesto ministra,

3455
01:44:39,080 --> 01:44:49,700
 isto tako radio u ministarstvu Slovačke između 2006. tijekom uvođena eura, no sad je vreme da čujemo i drugu stranu monetarne pliče.

3456
01:44:49,700 --> 01:44:54,920
 Ja sam malo radi vas upotpunio nešto da malo više saznate o samim našim govornicima.

3457
01:44:54,920 --> 01:45:01,620
 Dakle, gospodina Elena Kuhutikova, bivša zamjenica governera Sredinjšte banke Slovačke, diplomirala je u Bratislavi,

3458
01:45:01,620 --> 01:45:06,940
 radila kao glavni ekonomski istraživač na ekonomskom institutu, gdje je završila je posle diplomski strudi,

3459
01:45:06,940 --> 01:45:13,860
 radila je čak i u Čehoslovačkoj Središnjoj banci, najprije kao bankarski stručnjak, a potem kao direktor odljela za bankovne transakcije,

3460
01:45:13,860 --> 01:45:19,820
 onda nakon toga u Središnjoj banci Slovačke, u oživku 2000. predstavnik Republike Slovačke,

3461
01:45:19,820 --> 01:45:22,940
 imenuje zamjenicom guvernera Sredinjšnje banke Slovačke.

3462
01:45:22,940 --> 01:45:28,020
 Od 2006. nam radi u VUB banci, to je dio Intesa San Paolo Grupe,

3463
01:45:28,020 --> 01:45:31,900
 i kao član upravnog odbora i zamjenica glavnog izvršnog direktora.

3464
01:45:31,900 --> 01:45:36,560
 Gospodina Kuhutikova je jedna od najvećih stručnjaka u Slovačkoj za uvođenje eura,

3465
01:45:36,560 --> 01:45:40,060
 ili kako su je u Slovačkoj znali tepati madame eura.

3466
01:45:40,060 --> 01:45:42,880
 Podsjetimo, Slovačka je uvjela 2009. godine.

3467
01:45:42,880 --> 01:45:47,180
 Razlog za odobir sljedeća dva panelista vrlo je jednostavan.

3468
01:45:47,180 --> 01:45:49,560
 Dakle, Slovenija je prva od novih zemalja proširenja,

3469
01:45:49,820 --> 01:45:51,540
 koja je uvjela euro.

3470
01:45:51,540 --> 01:45:55,200
 Dakle, samo, mogli bi reći, tri, formalno tri,

3471
01:45:55,200 --> 01:45:58,140
 ali zapravo dvije godine nakon stupanja u članstvo, 2004.

3472
01:45:58,140 --> 01:46:02,420
 Prvi slovenski panelist je gospodin Darko Bohnec,

3473
01:46:02,420 --> 01:46:04,220
 bivši vice guverner Banke Slovenije.

3474
01:46:04,220 --> 01:46:06,720
 Isto tako diplomiruo u Ljubljani,

3475
01:46:06,720 --> 01:46:09,220
 probao petgodno u Ministarstvu financija Slovenije,

3476
01:46:09,220 --> 01:46:12,140
 pridružio se Slovenskoj narodnoj banci,

3477
01:46:12,140 --> 01:46:14,220
 odnosno Banka Slovenije se kod njih zove.

3478
01:46:14,220 --> 01:46:16,440
 Bili ste na čelu dva odjela,

3479
01:46:16,440 --> 01:46:19,220
 od 89. do 92. odjela analize istraživosti,

3480
01:46:19,820 --> 01:46:21,820
 od 94. do 98.

3481
01:46:21,820 --> 01:46:27,020
 Aha, they tell me that I should switch to English.

3482
01:46:27,020 --> 01:46:28,820
 Okay, I try to...

3483
01:46:28,820 --> 01:46:32,640
 But this introduction was just for the purpose

3484
01:46:32,640 --> 01:46:35,440
 of our audience, the mainly Croats,

3485
01:46:35,440 --> 01:46:39,260
 and I can finish in Croatian,

3486
01:46:39,260 --> 01:46:43,320
 then we will switch to English for panel.

3487
01:46:43,820 --> 01:46:45,520
 But I do understand

3488
01:46:45,520 --> 01:46:47,860
 that you are quite good

3489
01:46:47,860 --> 01:46:48,800
 in Croatian language,

3490
01:46:48,800 --> 01:46:50,580
 as it should be.

3491
01:46:50,580 --> 01:46:53,060
 And at the end,

3492
01:46:53,060 --> 01:46:57,160
 last but not least,

3493
01:46:57,160 --> 01:46:58,700
 the panelist, Mr. Igor Masten,

3494
01:46:58,700 --> 01:47:00,300
 who is Igor Masten,

3495
01:47:00,960 --> 01:47:04,880
 it's the easiest way to answer this,

3496
01:47:04,880 --> 01:47:07,880
 he is professor for the last 17 years or so.

3497
01:47:07,880 --> 01:47:11,280
 But then you could ask,

3498
01:47:11,280 --> 01:47:13,960
 why should we add someone

3499
01:47:13,960 --> 01:47:15,760
 who is on a theoretical,

3500
01:47:15,760 --> 01:47:17,080
 not on a practical side

3501
01:47:17,080 --> 01:47:18,100
 of introducing the euro?

3502
01:47:18,100 --> 01:47:22,900
 Well, according to his CV,

3503
01:47:23,380 --> 01:47:26,260
 he is not a typical ex-cathedra professor,

3504
01:47:26,260 --> 01:47:28,160
 as I see.

3505
01:47:28,160 --> 01:47:33,280
 The field of interest is very wide.

3506
01:47:33,280 --> 01:47:36,920
 Besides, you are an active partner

3507
01:47:36,920 --> 01:47:38,920
 and grant orton advisory,

3508
01:47:38,920 --> 01:47:42,180
 you were head of research

3509
01:47:42,180 --> 01:47:43,840
 of Bank of Slovenia,

3510
01:47:44,660 --> 01:47:46,860
 and then vice president

3511
01:47:46,860 --> 01:47:49,480
 of supervisory board of Hydria.

3512
01:47:49,480 --> 01:47:52,160
 It's about automotive

3513
01:47:52,160 --> 01:47:53,740
 and industrial technology,

3514
01:47:53,740 --> 01:47:57,740
 which has 1,800 workers

3515
01:47:57,740 --> 01:48:00,160
 working in five countries,

3516
01:48:00,160 --> 01:48:02,460
 Slovenia, Germany,

3517
01:48:02,460 --> 01:48:04,040
 Hungary, China,

3518
01:48:04,040 --> 01:48:06,600
 and your products are sold

3519
01:48:06,600 --> 01:48:08,600
 in 55 countries around the world.

3520
01:48:08,600 --> 01:48:09,700
 And, of course,

3521
01:48:10,580 --> 01:48:13,580
 you were the board member

3522
01:48:13,580 --> 01:48:15,160
 of NLB Bank,

3523
01:48:15,160 --> 01:48:16,540
 head of risk committee,

3524
01:48:16,540 --> 01:48:19,160
 and a member

3525
01:48:19,160 --> 01:48:21,740
 of a strategic council

3526
01:48:21,740 --> 01:48:23,640
 for economic development

3527
01:48:23,640 --> 01:48:25,040
 of Republic of Slovenia.

3528
01:48:25,040 --> 01:48:26,840
 That was during

3529
01:48:26,840 --> 01:48:30,300
 the introduction of Europe.

3530
01:48:30,300 --> 01:48:33,060
 So, well,

3531
01:48:33,060 --> 01:48:36,020
 we will start

3532
01:48:36,020 --> 01:48:38,380
 with Ms. Kohutnikova.

3533
01:48:39,820 --> 01:48:42,000
 We hear a lot

3534
01:48:42,000 --> 01:48:42,800
 of different stories

3535
01:48:42,800 --> 01:48:44,060
 about the cost-benefit.

3536
01:48:44,060 --> 01:48:46,100
 What is the greatest benefit

3537
01:48:46,100 --> 01:48:47,600
 of introducing euro

3538
01:48:47,600 --> 01:48:49,140
 in Slovakia?

3539
01:48:49,140 --> 01:48:50,220
 What was?

3540
01:48:50,220 --> 01:48:53,000
 Thank you, Senzik, a lot.

3541
01:48:53,000 --> 01:48:53,620
 Firstly,

3542
01:48:53,620 --> 01:48:54,500
 I would like to thank

3543
01:48:54,500 --> 01:48:56,580
 the National Bank of Croatia

3544
01:48:56,580 --> 01:48:57,720
 for inviting me here.

3545
01:48:57,720 --> 01:48:59,340
 And I would like

3546
01:48:59,340 --> 01:49:01,580
 to make some points clear.

3547
01:49:01,580 --> 01:49:03,640
 Slovakia is a country

3548
01:49:03,640 --> 01:49:05,340
 that didn't experience

3549
01:49:05,340 --> 01:49:06,200
 high proliferation,

3550
01:49:06,200 --> 01:49:08,000
 didn't experience

3551
01:49:08,000 --> 01:49:09,440
 double currency,

3552
01:49:09,440 --> 01:49:11,500
 in circulation

3553
01:49:11,500 --> 01:49:13,320
 or double currency economy,

3554
01:49:13,320 --> 01:49:15,140
 and didn't experience

3555
01:49:15,140 --> 01:49:16,720
 a huge fiscal debt.

3556
01:49:16,720 --> 01:49:19,100
 From this point of view,

3557
01:49:19,100 --> 01:49:20,860
 we do not have

3558
01:49:20,860 --> 01:49:22,200
 this knowledge

3559
01:49:22,200 --> 01:49:23,420
 or this experience

3560
01:49:23,420 --> 01:49:24,260
 that you have.

3561
01:49:24,260 --> 01:49:25,120
 That means

3562
01:49:25,120 --> 01:49:26,260
 the only currency

3563
01:49:26,260 --> 01:49:27,440
 and all loans

3564
01:49:27,440 --> 01:49:29,140
 and majority of deposit,

3565
01:49:29,140 --> 01:49:30,600
 almost all majority

3566
01:49:30,600 --> 01:49:30,980
 of deposit,

3567
01:49:30,980 --> 01:49:32,060
 were in Slovakia.

3568
01:49:32,060 --> 01:49:32,420
 in Slovakia.

3569
01:49:32,420 --> 01:49:34,680
